HLPSTART {
[1;36mTopic: Start playing Galactic Empire 

When you begin playing Galactic Empire you are first given an Interceptor-class
ship. The Interceptor is ideal to begin your quest into the galaxy. You can
seek out an ideal planet to colonize, claim it, and transport down a basic
compliment of colonists and supplies.

After starting your colony, give it some time to grow. Your planet's population
will soon be large enough to generate taxes and put cash in your pocket. With
this cash you can purchase more powerful ships and additional goods to expand
your empire. 

Additionally, you can engage in combat with other ships. Cybertrons and other
automated ships are plentiful in the galaxy, and if you can destroy them you
will receive a portion of the goods they were carrying. Always be prepared for
battle (or to flee), as the more powerful your ship is, the more Cybertrons
will be dispatched to intercept you.

As far as other (real life) players in the galaxy, you can engage in combat
with them or try to build alliances. A sneak attack on an unsuspecting fellow
player might bring short term gains, but long term trouble.

