HLPBATT3 {
[1;36mTopic: Battle strategy (section 3, planetary battles)

Planets can defend themselves with troops, fighters, and ion cannons. If you
have no troops or fighters, your planet can be easily overrun.

FIGHTERS are Nova-class battle fighters commanded by a fully automated tactical
computer. They have inboard and outboard photon cannons capable of powerful and
offensive and defensive attacks. However, due to galactic treaty, fighters
launched from a ship are not programmed to attack troops stationed on a planet.

TROOPS are trained mercenaries, and serve no other function than the defense of
